    "body": "spotted also here: https://github.com/coder/coder/actions/runs/9856429623/job/27213431086\r\n\r\n```\r\n=== FAIL: coderd/database/dbpurge TestDeleteOldWorkspaceAgentLogs (0.22s)\r\n    t.go:99: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.115 [info]  pubsub: pubsub dialing postgres  network=tcp  address=127.0.0.1:5432  timeout_ms=0\r\n    t.go:99: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.115 [info]  pubsub: pubsub postgres TCP connection established  network=tcp  address=127.0.0.1:5432  timeout_ms=0  elapsed_ms=0\r\n    t.go:99: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.130 [info]  pubsub: pubsub connected to postgres\r\n    t.go:99: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.130 [info]  pubsub: pubsub has started\r\n    t.go:99: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.251 [info]  purged old database entries  duration=28.014231ms\r\n    t.go:102: 2024-07-09 11:49:21.251 [erro]  failed to purge old database entries ...\r\n        error= commit transaction:\r\n                   github.com/coder/coder/v2/coderd/database.(*sqlQuerier).runTx\r\n                       /home/runner/work/coder/coder/coderd/database/db.go:149\r\n                 - driver: bad connection\r\n```\r\n\r\nI might be wrong, but if 2 tests are running at the same time, they may try to lock `database.LockIDDBPurge` at the same time, hence `bad connection`? I will disable parallel tests to see if it improves.\r\n",
